Double-needle stitched bottom and sleeve hems. Shoulder-to-shoulder taping. Seamless rib collar. About The Band: (pronounced Ih-jee-un) The monstrosity Aegaeon was conceived in Indiana, during the summer of 2008 by members who all have years of band experience. Since it’s inception, the singular obsession of Aegaeon has been to spread the infection to as much of the world as possible. The band recorded their first EP in the summer of 2009, following an abundance of relentless writing, practicing and performing-cultivating a strong regional following. The first release by Aegaeon received an overwhelming response worldwide, selling copies all over the US as well as in Germany, Australia, Czech Republic, Canada, Finland, Russia, Chile and the UK. In late 2009 Aegaeon lost a guitarist, Jerry Grannan, but quickly got a replacement, a long time friend of all members of the band. With the fresh line-up, the band has already started to embark on constant national touring.
